      {
        "id": "kIqMQvcB3KnE4sm_",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Simulating your Muscles</strong></p><p>Did you know that your muscles work because of electrical signals?</p><p>When there are high electrical signals your muscles become flexed. When there are lower electrical signals, your muscles become relaxed.</p><p>Your muscle activity can be measured using electromyography (EMG).</p><p></p><p>We can simulate this with a generator: when the number is high, it’s like the person is gripping really hard, and when the number is low, it’s like they are relaxed.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
