      {
        "id": "AIXTCdcaarcU5oIo",
        "title": "Making the Gripper Work",
        "content": {
          "type": "Question",
          "version": 1,
          "locked": false,
          "questionId": "gbh60d",
          "tiles": [
            {
              "title": "Question Prompt",
              "fixedPosition": true,
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<p>In the simulation below you see a hand connected to a gripper (the orange thing that looks like it can open and close.)</p><p>Do you see the grey block that connects the hand to the gripper? That&#x27;s a computer chip. You will program the computer chip in the dataflow program underneath the simulation.</p><p></p><p>First, we just want to make the gripper work.</p><p>In the dataflow program you can see a block that controls the gripper.</p><p>Can you connect a generator to the program to make the gripper open and close?</p>"
                ]
